D.q[5620] = "Greetings. How is the questioning of the renegades going?";
D.q[2571] = "I can see at youw feet that you walked a long way to come visit me. So listen to me cawefully: among the Dofus awe fake ones... Genuine Dofus awe laid by dwagons. Only dummies can think a Cawwot lay eggs! The Cawwot Dofus is an enchanted Cawwot by Wa Wabbit which is giving him vewy powerful powers...";
D.q[2502] = "I can see you\'re tough when it comes to business... As they\'ve been worn already, I\'ll let you have them cheap...";
D.q[2550] = "I can tell from your look that you came to help us! (News circulates quite fast in Pandala!) All my Pandawas are busy at the moment and I need someone I can trust to bring those Bamboos to the Shield Smith.";
D.q[6353] = "Well done. Bontarian morale will take a blow when they find out they\'ve been slaughtered with their own weapons!";
D.q[1926] = "I completely forgot that we are going to use Mush Mush Thorns for today\'s invention... we might need some more for the tests... if you don\'t mind, I\'d like to get half a dozen of them...";
D.q[3253] = "I discreetly followed you as you travelled and I must say that I\'m quite impressed by your courage. I hope that you now realize how terrible and vain the Dofus quest can be as it can lead an entire village to ruins...\nIt\'s time for you to leave. Osamodas won\'t like what you\'ve done to his disciples!";
D.q[1982] = "I don\'t know who you are, but let me tell you, I doubt you\'ll get out of here as easily as you got in...";
D.q[2468] = "I don\'t have time to talk. Leave me alone...";
D.q[446] = "I don\'t need anything else. But I\'m collecting belts, Chance Belts to be exact. If you can find 100 of them, I\'ll give you a Small Intelligence Scroll.";
D.q[2837] = "Later!";
D.q[5169] = "I don\'t understand. Why does nobody want my beer! There\'s real iron filings inside there. It\'s beyond me.";
D.q[6758] = "What? I\'ve nothing to say to you.";
D.q[1343] = "I give up. You\'re too strong for me. I\'m gonna go fight some Arachnees instead.\nGwahahaha!";
D.q[2480] = "I find it weird that these bamboos split so easily. It\'s the first time I\'ve ever seen this - they look like their insides have been hollowed out by some bug. Fortunately, we Enutrofs know our job! We just need some amber and we can fix them in no time!";
D.q[3100] = "I\'ve no idea what this shark\'s looking for. A beer-marinated docker?";
D.q[495] = "I have no letters to send him right now.";
D.q[492] = "I have to send him messages on a regular basis. If you deliver this letter, I\'ll give you 200 Kamas and your reputation in our clan will grow.\nYou\'ll find him in the mountains.";
D.q[1875] = "I hope you know who the culprit is...";
D.q[3178] = "Hello there, adventurer! How are you? My name is Mawy. I was born on Wabbit Island and the famous Farle Ingalsse is my uncle. How mad is that? I bet you want to see inside my barn! You\'ll need a key to get in, I lost mine last week while wandering the fields with my lover. With a bit of luck, you\'ll find it, unless some vile monster already took it. If that\'s the case, you\'ll have to hunt it down and take it back!";
D.q[6321] = "For me? Oh thank you. So Amayiro is very happy with my work and he\'s giving me a bonus? Wow, and I thought I was so over the hill that I was only fit for Piwi taming. \nThat\'s not everything, but I\'ve work to finish and I\'ve to go see Two-fingers to sort out some important things. We\'ve just got some new ore in and the quality is higher than before. The new tools are great too. But it means I can\'t leave the forge empty so you\'ll have to get out of here. If you need me for anything, don\'t bother waiting around, you\'ll just have to come back later.";
D.q[2564] = "I know that one of them is riving in the ever forest. Find her and she\'d tar you which Dofus she\'s watching... that is if you don\'t descend into craziness! Furrow my piece of advice and go meditate in your temper to prepare yourself for this adventure. When you\'re in front of this creature, ask it this simper question: a rung time ago in the pupils of Razeriane a coror was refrecting... what was this coror? Bring the answer to the wise Lenald of Feudala! Good Ruck!";
D.q[3326] = "I know the perfect place for my new world map. My toilet... on the door, that is!";
D.q[2142] = "I know, I know! You\'ve already called in to me! My god, you\'re as forgetful as Joe - and you\'re not even half his age!?";
D.q[375] = "I mostly need Bluish Jelly - since it doesn\'t have much taste, you can add any flavour to it. But I need a lot of it, so I\'ll only buy it in batches of 100.";
D.q[6520] = "Why don\'t you pull up a stool and have a game. The crazier you are, the more you laugh. Ahahaha.";
D.q[2899] = "I must take care of the level passage of many others enthusiasts. Try coming back in four hours, at least!";
D.q[401] = "I need 45 Blue Larva skins, 45 Orange Larva skins, 45 Green Larva skins and 30 Evil Tofu wings.";
D.q[6527] = "Hello, did Oto Mustam send you?";
D.q[6529] = "Thank you, believe me when I say I\'ll never forget your mercy.";
D.q[1452] = "I said 10 barks at least!";
D.q[2280] = "I pray... We\'ve been made in the image of the gods who created us, and we should always listen to them... To understand that, I had to lose a bit of my ear, but I came round in the end.";
D.q[6702] = "Nothing to report.";
D.q[286] = "I say, I gulp down a cup of hot water every Thursday, with a drop of milk and a few leaves in it. Top hole, what what? Rather!";
D.q[2776] = "I see... you\'ve been recommended by a Temple master. I\'ll let you in then. But it will be the first and last time I make an exception!";
D.q[1583] = "I spent all my wages in the tailors\' district, well, my parent\'s wages, that is...";
D.q[3097] = "I shouldn\'t have drunk that so quickly. Some water will do me good.";
D.q[2664] = "I think I\'m going to build something to protect the entrance to the clock room. Too many people in this village are just walking right in!\n\nI can\'t give you much of my time. Ironic really, since I\'m the guardian of time! I can\'t take my eyes off those clocks.... What was it you wanted to say?";
D.q[1315] = "I understand, you want my lung of the plains. I\'d rather die than give it to you. Guaaaarrrds!";
D.q[6530] = "Thank you again for showing me mercy, your kind act will have much more impact that you think.";
D.q[2042] = "I was about to forget! Here, take this Gobball syringe. The needle isn\'t too thin but it should do the job, alright? Come back to see me when you have the blood. I\'ll know how to make it talk. Ha, only joking! After some analysis, I\'ll find out what struck this poor Enutrof down.";
D.q[3231] = "I watched you fight and honestly I\'m very impressed. No joke! You\'re shapeless, you\'ve got terrible tastes for clothes and I won\'t even mention your accent... You remind me of those southern ninnies! Fortunately, you know how to fight and it makes up for many other things...\nWell, I suppose that you want me to take you out of here?";
D.q[3510] = "I\'ll assemble an intelligent creature which will satisfy all my requirements.";
D.q[4489] = "I haven\'t seen him lately, but I know he\'s a very busy man. At least that\'s how it looks. Sorry I can\'t help you any more than that.";
D.q[4074] = "I\'d like to be able to dress up as a Koalak and for this I\'d simply need a Koalak set! \nBring me back a full Koalak set in good condition. Maybe then, I\'ll forgive you. \nIf I\'m in a good mood, I\'ll give you one of my old pets. It\'s hard to feed, bites pretty hard and smells a little. He\'s not beautiful enough for me but I think that it\'ll suit you.";
D.q[1283] = "Do you really want to fight me? If you\'re sure, follow me into the house.\nI\'ll show you the room where I train.";
D.q[2735] = "I\'d never set foot in such a place, NEVER! But I\'ve asked about the shortest way to get to the natives. Let me tell you I\'ve been very selective in my research. I only interviewed those who said they were returning from the forest and WHO HAD LIMBS MISSING.\nYou almost look like a nice person, so I think I can entrust you with this work. I never had time to finish it so you\'ll only find the way to get to the Dark Vlad Clearing. Anyway, I don\'t think there\'s anything else of interest.";
D.q[2446] = "I\'m all ears, which marketplace are you looking for?";
D.q[4880] = "Do you remember the magic horn found on Moon Island? Brakmar knows that we have it, but they don\'t yet know how powerful it is, so I\'ve come up with a plan to convince them that it\'s incredibly dangerous. I\'ll need people I can trust to make all this happen, though.\nGo find Captain Koda, Ture Inge, the jeweller Marge Gondersun and the militiaman Niamuh Boulkier.";
D.q[722] = "I\'m back #1, I congratulate you on behalf of my superiors.\nThis week I\'ll teach my guys how to handle a staff. For this, I\'ll need about twenty Twiggy Staffs... I know that you have some acquaintances in the staff carvers\' district. \nTake your time, training won\'t start for a few days.";
D.q[4580] = "One of my manuals, thank you. As promised, I\'ll help you, on the condition that you bring me what I need, which is a Magic Patch. A tailor will be able to make you one using this recipe. I also need some Magic Blood Orange Dye. This recipe isn\'t well known amongst alchemists as my friend Uba Tesse lost it somewhere in his house. But to thank you for bringing one of my manuals, I\'ll give it to you with pleasure.";
D.q[6511] = "A gaming room? I don\'t know what you ... Oh, it\'s you! I\'m sorry, a thousand apologies, I did not want to lie to you. It\'s just that... I can\'t talk about it to anyone, you understand? Here\'s a key so you can go there even if I\'m not here, the hidden entrance is at the back of the room. It\'s always a pleasure to receive a Brakmarian of your rank in our tavern. And look, if you\'re not too busy, my shift finishes between 21:30 and 22:00...";
D.q[6519] = "A Sram, you say? Yeah, that rings a bell, I\'ve noticed her around once or twice. In fact the last time I came she bagged a big load of Kamas and a brawl broke out. Of course I didn\'t participate in this brawl, what you take me for? I ... I did not have my weapon on me then, uh, you know what, I preferred to stay back and watch to make sure the fight did not get out of hand.";
D.q[3068] = "I\'m quite unlucky with the ladies. Okay, I want you to invite my buddy Walt Apain instead. Bring me back some beer when you can too.";
D.q[3127] = "Ah, #1, you\'re finally here! \nI\'m Oshar Marif, the famous Dragoturkey Breeder! Dragoturkeys are my passion! \nI\'m happy to see that you\'ve finally made it here to set me free. I lost a terrible fight against the Koolich and I\'m so exhausted that I can\'t make it back to the village on my own. I need someone to help me...";
D.q[4067] = "I\'m sorry but you don\'t have the necessary ingredients for me to create the right potion.";
D.q[3128] = "The only thing that could help me recover my strength would be some herbal tea made from Kaliptus leaves.\nYou seem surprised, #1! Surely everybody knows that Kaliptus herbal tea gives you a boost! I tell you what, if you bring me back 50 Kaliptus Leaves and 50 Kaliptus Flowers, I\'ll share my vast knowledge on Dragoturkeys with you, after I\'ve had my herbal tea, of course!";
D.q[4583] = "You look a bit too pale to be a member of the Brakmarian Militia. Have you swallowed a Kralove the wrong way, by any chance?\nAh, you\'ve brought me the documents that the Bontarian stole, but there should be three of you, no? I suppose the two others stopped off at the inn. Go and join them, I\'ll pass these documents on to Kaffra Keeper as soon as he comes out of his meditation.";
D.q[1953] = "I\'m the beer delivery man. I wanted to drop by today, so I did! You have a problem with that?";
D.q[3160] = "Hi #1. I\'m Klako, one of the best Dragoturkey hunters in the land. My friend Oshar Marif, the famous breeder, ventured into the Koolich Cavern and never came back. If you could go there and try to help him out or bring me back his remains, I\'ll be extremely grateful. But only grateful, don\'t expect anything else from me. Not even a discount on my steaks!";
D.q[6374] = "You want to know what turtles eat, eh? Well, they start by chowing down on idiots like you. Hohoho.\nWhat, you\'re being serious? Oh, I see. Well. I know something that they just can\'t get enough of, oh yes. Fish on a bed of salad. I\'ll write the recipe down on the sand for you. Hohoho, my little boat. Will that do you?";
D.q[6381] = "I sense angew smouldewing in you. You\'we fwustwated with youw weaknesses and wish that people would admiwe and feaw you? Embwace the dawk side and evewything will become easiew. People will wowship at youw feet, youw enemies will twemble when they heaw youw name, you\'ll hawness a powew beyond compwehension.";
D.q[7065] = "Later. I\'m in the middle of a game of Rock, Paper, Scissors with Thomas Sacre and he\'s only winning by one point.";
D.q[6667] = "Listen to me carefully, what I\'m about to say is for your ears only. No one else can find out because I\'m risking my life and you your head, understand? Go and see Amayiro, in the Bontarian Militia, tell him I sent you.";
D.q[4596] = "That\'s terrible! They caught up with him. It\'s a pity you weren\'t able to defeat them...\nOto Mustam must be looking for the Fogornleg Horn too, why else would he steal the documents? We\'ve still got a small head start on our enemies, we should make the most of it.";
D.q[4098] = "I\'ve heard about a wold where my blothers and sisters are hunted for theil ful. That is just lidiculous!";
D.q[1432] = "I\'ve nothing to tell you #1, I\'m too busy anyway.";
D.q[4491] = "Brakmar is trying to take control of the Bay of Cania and the Dopple Territory so as to block access to the port and pillage the maritime traffic in the area. I\'ve already sent a patrol there and I\'d like you to throw your weight behind them. When the battle is over, report to Justfa Lafs and come back here.";
D.q[2503] = "I\'ve told you again and again that you pay the tax when you buy a Pandawa hat...";
D.q[3860] = "If you find a Snoowolf skin on your trip round Incarnam, bring it here. I\'ll find something to trade, friend.";
D.q[3602] = "Many other professions exist, but I only happen to know these. If you want to learn the others, you\'ll have to travel round the world and find other masters. There are some famous ones in Astrub.";
D.q[1796] = "If you want to challenge a Dopple, you must make a donation to the Ecaflip temple.\nIt will cost you a Trout.";
D.q[5614] = "Greetings. Has the Terra family agreed to help us?";
D.q[1797] = "If you want to challenge a Dopple, you must make a donation to the Ecaflip temple.\nIt will cost you a Carp Ediem.";
D.q[1781] = "If you want to challenge a Dopple, you must make a donation to the Feca temple.\nIt will cost you Gobball War Chief Wool.";
D.q[1675] = "Very well, now turn the Gobball Wheel!";
D.q[1824] = "If you want to challenge a Dopple, you must make a donation to the Sram temple.\nIt will cost you Plain Boar leather.";
D.q[1825] = "If you want to challenge a Dopple, you must make a donation to the Sram temple.\nIt will cost you Lousy Pig Leather.";
D.q[637] = "If you\'re looking for recipes, you should go to the library. An alchemist created an encyclopedia composed of more than 12 books about rare recipes.";
D.q[3752] = "If you want to learn another profession, go and see Gilles in the Inn workshop. He\'ll be able to help you out.";
D.q[5782] = "SATISFACTION!\nI love my ring of SATISFACTION!\nAnd my boots of SATISFACTION!\nAnd...";
D.q[1854] = "Oh really? You\'re so sweet my dear. But be careful, they\'re not as gentle as they look! Oh my, Kweeky will be so happy.";
D.q[2816] = "Is it for an offering to the goddess?";
D.q[1992] = "It got her out of the coma. However, her senses are still mixed up. What can we do? Can you go back to Nepra? I\'ll try and keep her conscious while you\'re away.";
D.q[1541] = "Ha, I see you\'ve received my message...\nIn fact, the favour I\'ve to ask you is quite simple. Elections are approaching and I\'d like you to question Paro Cabane to know if I\'ll be re-elected or not... \nMost of his predictions proved to be true so you can trust him.";
D.q[4246] = "It\'s a lovely night, isn\'t it?";
D.q[3202] = "The labyrinth is very complicated, so listen carefully!\nYou must be on one of these slabs to enter the corresponding room. The labyrinth has 25 rooms, which form a large square. When hitting the switch you won\'t open the doors of the room you\'re in, but the doors of the next room, so you\'ll need to get other adventurers to open your doors. That bit\'s easy enough, right?";
D.q[1878] = "Marp is a bit of a joker. Deep down she\'s nice, but between you and me, she\'s a bit strange.";
D.q[950] = "May I help you?";
D.q[2040] = "It\'s no use coming back if you don\'t have a sword, young lop!";
D.q[685] = "It\'s an icon carefully venerated\nYour spirit has now ascended\nYou\'ll also need to work on your communication\nWhich will be necessary to this communion";
D.q[2493] = "It\'s nice here, isn\'t it ?";
D.q[7073] = "Don\'t you think that rock looks like a sinking ship? No? Strange... Sometimes I\'ve these silent visions where I\'m on the bow of a ship, the foam caressing my face... hey, look, what do you want?";
D.q[3115] = "It\'s not that hard to deliver potatoes, is it?";
D.q[960] = "May I help you?";
D.q[951] = "May I help you?";
D.q[4187] = "It\'s only a nickname that the Black and Pink Knight gave me ... it\'s not my real name, I\'m not Miss Lousy Piggy!\nI want my revenge! That boor ruined my reputation as a Scarplane pilot... Please, do something!\nCould you go and make a fool of him for me?";
D.q[1958] = "It\'s your choice darling... But I don\'t ever remember my master letting a piece of meat slip out of his hands. \nSeriously though, be nice! I could get in trouble!";
D.q[397] = "It\'s very kind of you... well, kind is perhaps not the right word, given I\'m going to pay you... but you\'re useful. Yes, it\'s very useful of you. Well then, what I need is 60 Blue Larva skins, 50 Orange Larva skins, 50 Green Larva skins, 40 Malefic Tofu Wings and 30 units of Vampire Blood.\nIf you can bring me all this, I\'ll give you a powerful scroll.";
D.q[2427] = "Jewellers make all kinds of rings and necklaces, often imbuing them with magical powers. From the simplest metal ring to the most terrifyingly powerful necklace, jewellers channel the elemental forces found in special metals and other materials. This profession requires more skill and patience than most.";
D.q[1034] = "What can Musa the Wolf shooter do for you?";
D.q[676] = "Learn what? You want to learn how to knit? You\'ve come to the right place. I mean no! You\'ve come to the WRONG place. I only do embroidery! It\'s my secret talent... Do you want to learn my secret talent, too?";
D.q[2243] = "Let me rest... bring the wood to my apprentice, he\'ll know what to do.";
D.q[1046] = "Let\'s not beat around the bush my friend. Now tell me, how much powder do you need?";
D.q[1978] = "Let\'s see heeere... No no nooooo! Now that won\'t do at all! You\'re not even wearing a hood, silly. You... you have to look like a meanie. That doesn\'t say meanie... that says... honest. Poo! You smell like honest honey!";
D.q[3524] = "Litol must become first goblinmagus.";
D.q[1981] = "Locette serves in the militia. She came back from one of her expeditions with some kind of disease. All food has been tasteless to her ever since. The doctor found nothing. The next day, her ears were ringing and we could only communicate by writing. Then her sight went... and her speech...and she ended up fainting...";
D.q[3183] = "Lord Crow is walking up and down through the rooms in this library. Fortunately for you, I\'ll stay with you in each room to help you locate Lord Crow. don\'t hesitate to come to me and ask me where he\'s when you feel lost.";
D.q[2152] = "Marp, explain this to me right now!";
D.q[3146] = "May Rushu burn what\'s left of your conscience!\nHow dare you attack such young and fragile Sadidettes!\nYou even broke my boomerang! I\'ll have to wait until my next birthday to get a new one from our Master Skeunk! \nGet out of here, you child-batterer!";
D.q[3482] = "Me alone in the world, poor abandoned KrazyBwork.";
D.q[1726] = "Ecaflips can use any weapon, but they handle swords and daggers best.";
D.q[2845] = "Mmmh... I wouldn\'t mind a little nap...";
D.q[2742] = "May a thousand bamboos be pleasing to your backbone, noble adventurer! You seem to be quite nice, so let me tell you something...";
D.q[2930] = "May the holy fire come to you, may its heat comfort you and its divine flame enlighten you!";
D.q[466] = "Molning, you\'ve tlavelled far my young fliend. Can I take you somewhele?";
D.q[1727] = "Eniripsas can use any weapon, but they handle wands and staffs best.";
D.q[6503] = "I\'m being transferred to the Tower of Bonta? \nWhatever you say!\nI\'ve to arrest everyone who leaves the tower?\nWhatever you say!";
D.q[6082] = "I don\'t understand what\'s going on in Rosal\'s head. It couldn\'t be clearer that Brakmar is humanity\'s enemy.";
D.q[1051] = "Nah, Don\'t wanna talk toya, yar too meen! An\' me mouz too dry to talk anyway.";
D.q[6888] = "I promised to take care of him, sniff. What will I do now that he is gone? I have failed in my duty as an Eniripsa, all that\'s left is for me to cut my wings off and jump into the Bottomless Peat Bog. I\'ll probably be reincarnated as a Miremop to redeem myself to my goddess.";
D.q[2906] = "Nice one, mercenary!";
D.q[2908] = "Nice one, mercenary!";
D.q[6939] = "At a session of frenzied shovel-rolling, my husband told me where to find the tile and how to activate its magic.\nHe buried it north-east of here, at the foot of a Dragoturkey statue. Only a Enutrof with a Crackler\'s Golden Tooth in their inventory and wearing an Enutrof\'s Memento can activate its magic.\nIf it helps, write down whatever you need to remember the information, and don\'t forget our deal when you see the medium.";
D.q[1386] = "Nothing to report here.";
D.q[1389] = "Nothing to report here.";
D.q[6922] = "Why didn\'t I go looking for her? Because Nosilla was beset by more and more visions, which made her less and less reliable in combat, not to mention the state of depression she sank inexorably into.\nIn addition, when she had expressed her intention to isolate herself, I wasn\'t worried when she unexpectedly disappeared.\nIf you really want to learn more, go and ask Grizmine. He and Nosilla were very close. I haven\'t seen that Ecaflip for ages because between training sessions in the Primitive Cemetery, my excursions in the Bworker dungeon, my training in the arena and my research into Count Harebourg, I just haven\'t had the time to look him up.\nFrom what I know, Grizmine keeps himself to himself in the Amakna Inn.\nGood luck with your search, keep me up to date with how it goes on.";
D.q[6083] = "Many Protectors are wandering far from the right path, but I don\'t want to talk about that anymore.";
D.q[2675] = "May you choke on the froth of the celestial pint! You and your descendants for centuries and centuries! You\'re off to a good start in life... In fact, you don\'t have any choice!";
D.q[713] = "Maybe you can help me again. I\'ve heard Lady Marmalade, the manageress of the Bagrutte Inn, is being harassed by a drunkard lately. Could you go see her and get some information on what really happened? You\'ll find the Inn in the northwest of the city.";
D.q[2033] = "Maybe you can help me now... Something spooky is going on in this town! But if you keep a cool head, everything will be fine. I know that weird things can happen in the underpasses...";
D.q[7143] = "Maybe you don\'t know where our temple is. Nothing could be more simple. You just have to open the map. All class buildings, as well as all temples, appear on it.";
D.q[3560] = "Me be chief and you no!";
D.q[3562] = "Me be Bwork chief! You give gift, me chief!";
D.q[5473] = "Me coming sometime, me like Park. Me like Park and Apples! ... and funny stories also!";
D.q[3499] = "Me don\'t like loudmouth.";
D.q[3491] = "Me headache, *yawns and rubs his head* Me search mummy.";
D.q[5475] = "Me like park and goooood aaaapple and funny storiiies!";
D.q[5472] = "Me like little Park!";
D.q[3518] = "Me want to eat your heart, not mine!";
D.q[3630] = "Me no want to go with you. Me prefer Piwi feather to Gobrator.";
D.q[3611] = "Me vibrate for her!";
D.q[1473] = "Ok, now that you know how the sewers are, you can go farther away.";
D.q[1170] = "Okay, off you go. I\'ll be waiting.";
D.q[4100] = "Which spell do you want to unlearn?";
D.q[3436] = "One day, I\'ll go on my own adventure.";
D.q[4010] = "Me, serve a prince? I\'d love to, sir, but unfortunately I don\'t have the appropriate attire...";
D.q[5461] = "You know story with polar bear going to tavern?";
D.q[3613] = "Pinkgob locked up under Bwork camp.";
D.q[3610] = "Pfff... You more weak than me! Go away.";
D.q[3723] = "Piwi piwi piwi?";
D.q[1902] = "Hey you, young Feca! Stop daydreaming! You look like you just fell off the moon! I could use some help, you know!";
D.q[7611] = "Hello, I\'m Harrysch wife. If you give me 3 schmall Kwischmasch preschentsch, I\'ll give you a medium schized one in return, and if you give me 3 medium schized preschentsch, I\'ll give you a big one in return. \nJuscht exchange with me and drop the correct number of preschentsch into the exchange window. \nIf I don\'t give you anything in return, it\'sch becausche the quantity or the type of item ischn\'t correct.";
D.q[4003] = "Me? Cook for a Wabbit? But they only eat raw cawwots! There\'s no point! You\'ll have to make more of an effort to motivate me.";
D.q[1851] = "Meow! \n*This Bow Meow looks happy*";
D.q[3973] = "Me? Kill a Wabbit? No I\'ve got way too much research to do to create my lovely partner already!";
D.q[1842] = "Meeeooow! \n*This Bow Meow looks sad!*";
D.q[4714] = "";
D.q[2919] = "Hello there, assassin. What brings you to your Order Master?";
D.q[1687] = "Since I heard you need a lot of Trool Tokens to enter the Gladiatrool, I\'ve started to save up.";
D.q[4319] = "Ok, tell the boss I\'ll be finished the jewel soon.";
D.q[3432] = "Sniff, my children, Hans! Gret! Where are you?";
D.q[1588] = "So be it.";
D.q[3414] = "I must tell you that the last time I saw a candle was on a dark miner\'s helmet. You\'ll have your work cut out for you there.";
D.q[3371] = "Metamunch sent you to me that I could put your valour to the test. Let\'s see now... I\'ve a task worthy of the greatest of warriors. Pay attention, I\'ll only say this once. It will be difficult, long and extremely dangerous, I\'ve dedicated my entire life to this... you may do the same yourself, young adventurer. Whatever the case, I ask you to carry out what work I give you with the utmost of attention. Let\'s start from the beginning. Here is a key. Find the door it\'s supposed to open. Go inside and confront the master. Come back to me if you still have legs to walk.";
D.q[4161] = "The last time I saw her, she was running away towards this village. I tried to catch her but she was too fast and determined. \nI think you could find her for me and then explain to me why she left.\nBut be careful, you\'ll probably have to fight against the creatures of the village to find her.";
D.q[3167] = "Last time I saw Lord Crow, he was in Library room number 1...\n\nLord Crow is in 9720!";
D.q[3925] = "So, who is this suitor?";
D.q[4908] = "Don\'t hang around, they must be hungry!";
D.q[4357] = "Have I seen any Ecaflips recently? Yes, I had one in here... spend the night playing and drinking, he didn\'t have a penny left by morning and I think the doorman kicked him out... can\'t remember why. Is that any help?";
D.q[3589] = "What can you do? Cut wood? That\'s good. I always need planks to fix the roof of the barn or reinforce the fence. Go cut down some trees in the forest.";
D.q[670] = "Metarias are raw materials. Wrought by alchemists, they can be used to make powerful elemental potions which will enable you to impregnate items with various elements. My last works show the effectiveness of this method on weapons, as well as the difficulties involved in mixing reality with magic. That\'s why I developed a method to help me do it... but I only teach it to some people.\n";
D.q[4946] = "So how are operations coming along in Amakna?";
D.q[2009] = "You really wanna train me? Well... okay... I guess a play fight won\'t hurt me. Anyways, I\'m not as weak as daddy thinks... Get ready... hey maybe I\'ll beat ya!";
D.q[1868] = "So?";
D.q[5013] = "This judge really is an insistent fellow. I\'m going to have a look! *Cracks the whip*";
D.q[5059] = "Go to Wabbit Island and find me someone who could transmit my orders to the islanders.";
D.q[3433] = "Really? It\'s so sweet of you! The children were playing at the fountain in the village. I was chatting with a friend and when I looked around, they were gone. I\'ve looked for them everywhere... I\'m so worried about them.";
D.q[5066] = "I am proud to belong to Bonta\'s militia.";
D.q[1862] = "For the hoops, I need a solid base, a boar\'s tusk that I\'ll surround with a tasteful fabric... yes, that\'s it... two boar fabrics. Sorry hon, I\'m thinking out loud... okay. Two Prespic peaks for the middle of the masks, and some fur for the soft seed... And to finish - the hardest part for the softest piece - get me a piece of Miliboowolf. You should find all that in the forest nearby, it\'ll be soooo worth it, I swear... Alit never tells fibs.";
D.q[2820] = "Sorry... You haven\'t paid the tax... I can\'t talk to you...";
D.q[1223] = "Stop! You shall not pass!";
D.q[5174] = "Test";
D.q[5229] = "I\'ve never seen that... never!";
D.q[5227] = "So? What was Divad\'s reply?";
D.q[5248] = "Did you find anything?";
D.q[5252] = "Jiva the wise";
D.q[5507] = "You\'ve got it wrong! I\'m an honest Sram!";
D.q[1993] = "Thank you so much! Locette feels good ever since, she just needs to rest a little more to get her senses back.";
D.q[5599] = "*sleeping*";
D.q[3324] = "Thank you, young adventurer!";
D.q[3329] = "Thank you, young adventurer!";
D.q[1843] = "Miaow?                        \n*You don\'t understand what he wants. Maybe he\'s thirsty? He probably needs a bowl of mimilk.*";
D.q[1174] = "Oh I see, Bhan Laka\'s bait. Take it and hurry up, he\'s not known for his patience.";
D.q[1183] = "Hem, what a pukey smell? Must be time for grandma\'s... ahem...\nHello there, can I help you?";
D.q[1224] = "A deal?\nWith 10,000 Kamas maybe we could find some common ground...";
D.q[1263] = "But you haven\'t even got 1,000 Kamas! Come back again when you\'re richer... a lot richer. 1,000 Kamas or no deal.";
D.q[3400] = "Mission completed. Bzztt... Your new mi... bztt kriiiik! Frtrtttt";
D.q[3401] = "Mission completed. Bzztt... Your new mi... bztt kriiiik! Frtrtttt";
D.q[3402] = "Mission completed. Bzztt... Your new mi... bztt kriiiik! Frtrtttt";
D.q[3405] = "Mission completed. Bzztt... Your new mi... bztt kriiiik! Frtrtttt";
D.q[6562] = "Mmm, I see you, you\'re smiling, right? I can feel you, you\'re planning something nasty. Did you poison the food? I\'m going to throw it away just in case. And the beer smells too much of ammonia... or not enough, it\'s strange. I\'m going to throw that out too.\nI\'ve thought a lot about it and I\'ve decided what I want. It\'s very simple and you should have no trouble getting it. I want a Dragobutt in Purple Bwork Leather. I\'ve had the last one for a long time now and I need a new one, I\'m starting to chafe from all the rubbing. Why are you looking at me like that? Was it something I said?";
D.q[3592] = "Mmmm. So you play around with flasks and potions? Me, I don\'t need that bother! Go get a couple of flax flowers so I can make some bread, then maybe we can talk.";
D.q[3536] = "Mmm, a Cra. I can see from a distance you\'re talented. A good bow, a nice, straight sightline and WHCHHHTBING!... your enemies are stuck to the wall! You\'ll love it. Wait there, I\'ve got something real special for you.";
D.q[6121] = "Mmmh... I see, nothing too glorious then. In any case, you managed to complete the missions I gave you and for this you deserve a place as a Guardian of Knowledge. Your knowledge will guide your comrades.";
D.q[1340] = "Give me that locket back!";
D.q[1419] = "I\'ve heard that many Amaknean villagers have gone to the East to join the war between Bonta and Brakmar.\nFor a few days, I\'ll be offering to change the identity papers of those who have deserted and want to come back to the Province.\nOn the other hand, I can\'t help officers because they will be easily spotted...";
D.q[1422] = "It\'s possible to return to Amakna to live, but if you do, you\'ll lose your rank in the militia along with all the advantages linked to it. Once you\'ve made your decision, you need to change your identity papers and to register again in the Amakna register. You\'ll also have to pay taxes according to your current rank.";
D.q[1431] = "I always found it tiring having to walk for miles to find a peaceful patch, so I\'ve created my own peaceful patch. I put loads of fish in it, too. Have a look!";
D.q[1560] = "Moo oom foond\'om morocl\'om sqoorrol\'om nord\'om ost\'om oxtorom bontom moo oom.";
D.q[852] = "More and more officers are saying good things about you. I\'m proud that one of my disciples has gained such fame. Go on like this... But don\'t get a big head. You\'re still nothing more than a larva grovelling before my boots! Just to make sure you remember that, I want you to kill 40 Blue Larvae and bring their eyes to me.";
D.q[1436] = "Actually, I\'ve put every fish I could find in there... Things got a little spicy and a new species has appeared. I named it Snapper.";
D.q[3707] = "More and more adventurers pass through Incarnam before heading to the country of Amakna.";
D.q[2163] = "Morning! I guess you\'re interested in buying a weapon? Sorry but I\'m up to my eyes in orders. Come back when worms can fly...erf!";
D.q[1106] = "Move on. I\'m not here to fight. I just want my swords back.";
D.q[1643] = "Multijely? It\'s a cursed crossbreed of jelly sweets. Nobody sells it anymore... since all those children disappeared that one time. Rumour has it that if you eat it, you get a one way ticket to your worst nightmare... and back.";
D.q[1342] = "You shall not pass! Damn Bontarians!";
D.q[4231] = "Much of our past has been lost but we believe that recreating the conditions that existed at that time is our only hope of revealing the ultimate mysteries of life itself. We believed we could control what we uncovered. This... creature we created... it has escaped.";
D.q[2522] = "Mumble... humongous profits... mumble... heaps of Kamas...";
D.q[2521] = "Mumble... Legend... mumblemumble... gwahahaha! mumble... flood the market... mumble... Grandapan....";
D.q[1498] = "Hum? May I ask you why you\'re swaying your hips like that in front of me? I asked you to put on official clothes, not to go shopping for a nice dress! Come back when you have the uniform.";
D.q[1590] = "Beave us abone, bon\'t you see bhat we\'re plabing bice?\nIb you wabba quib our bimension, use be mabic boor on the beft...";
D.q[1591] = "Bhat bo you want buman? How bare you bisturb me durinb this bame?";
D.q[6290] = "Mwahahaha! \nYou\'ve got a head for business, I must say. You know what you want. I heard that a group of youngsters were looking to get rid of an apparently unique and precious jewel. I can tell you where their hideout is, but you should be careful - you\'ll have to figure out how to get past all the security mechanisms to enter, and once you\'re there there\'s no guarantee that they\'ll play fair. You\'ll also need to go there with the disciples of several gods so as to find the way in. \nMwahahaha!";
D.q[1609] = "Hello! You look quite healthy! A perfect time for you to give us some blood. We need to keep a stock of blood in case a fighter gets hurt.";
D.q[1623] = "Do you want to try to catch the biggest Snapper? Ok! I can rent you a special Snapper fishing rod for only 100 Kamas.";
D.q[4307] = "My colleagues assisted me for many years in my researches, I\'d never have discovered so many things without them. I feel like I owe them something and I\'m glad that for my potions other adventurers can help them. \nI\'d like you to help the Professor Kalkulus, Stella Stukup, Polka Mere, Kito, the Doctor Nauh, Speet Fyer, Flip Flap and the Doctor Morose.";
D.q[1664] = "Dark Vlad hasn\'t resurfaced yet... \nFor 1,000 Kamas I can try to guess how long it\'s going to take him to reappear!";
D.q[4150] = "My colleagues wanted me to provide them with one of the best flours, the one made by Xavier the Baker!!\nBut it\'s way too hard to make so I thought I\'d mix a lot of different flours and just add a tiny bit of Xavier\'s. With a little bit of luck no one would ever notice! I had the idea but I\'m still missing the flours. Do you think you can help me out and get me what I need?";
D.q[989] = "My dream is nearly complete - my fair is a success.\nBut my head is still full of plans for new attractions. I won\'t be happy until everything\'s done!\n";
D.q[3909] = "My faithful friend, what a pleasure to see you!";
D.q[3060] = "They\'re still hungry! Some larva flesh should buck them up.";
D.q[4582] = "I should be able to fix this up for you, give me a moment.\n...\nThere you go, almost as good as new. I haven\'t been able to completely get rid of the smell of cawwots but it should fade with time.";
D.q[3735] = "As my friend Adidi always said, they must nest in the World of Twelve\'s darkest, narrowest passages. Dragons are paranoid creatures. If you discovered a dragon\'s den, it would be impossible to sneak in and steal its eggs, even by the back door. They hide their eggs jealously, just like an Enutrof with his very first gold nugget.";
D.q[1779] = "I\'ll teach you various things as you battle through your different missions.";
D.q[1784] = "Come back and see me later, when you know at least six spells of different classes...";
D.q[1401] = "Thhaaat\'ss peeerfeect tiimiing! Iiit sseeemms yoouu caan iideentiify thhe Bonntaariian whhooo attaaacked Braakmmar?";
D.q[1792] = "If you want to challenge a Dopple, you must make a donation to the Cra temple.\nIt will cost you some Cherry Wood.";
D.q[3741] = "Look at your compass! Adventure is that way!";
D.q[5640] = "What\'s your name? \nHey, I asked what your name is. Why won\'t you tell me?";
D.q[1846] = "*The Bow Meow eats slowly, then starts his moaning again.*\nMeeeooow...";
D.q[5631] = "I\'m praying to the goddess Eniripsa to shine her mercy down upon me. That way, I\'ll be able to heal my friends and devastate my enemies. Maybe I could do the opposite... hehe, wouldn\'t that be a hoot.";
D.q[3609] = "Ahh well my dear, this is just a small village. There are many more workshops down in Amakna!";
D.q[1847] = "*Maybe you can take him for a little walk around the village, it would do him good. \nIf you want a nice walk, you can go through the park, then smell the yummy cooked fish at the marketplace, then smell the florist\'s flowers, and finally you can come back here*";
D.q[3780] = "Do you wish to return to your statue, young one?";
D.q[4613] = "Bah, you\'re not allowed to answer with another question, that\'s cheating. Are you looking for the Fogornleg Horn too?\nWhat!? You\'re a pathetic Bontarian! Die, scum!";
D.q[3781] = "Do you wish to return to your statue, young one?";
D.q[3777] = "Do you wish to return to your statue, young one?";
D.q[3543] = "Hello, young Pandawa! Wait one minute... Show me your eyes! Not too sober yet... Perfect! In this state, you\'ll have no problem beating the hell out of your enemies. Take a good, strong axe, a few bottles of the good stuff... and fight!";
D.q[3694] = "Are you still looking for a job in the region?\nHonestly, if I were you I\'d go check in Astrub. You look like you can cope on your own.";
D.q[6514] = "Hey hey hey, have you got any Kamas for me? I\'ll tell you everything I know about Petra if you\'ve got some Kamas for me. Don\'t be a tightwad, give me all your Kamas!";
D.q[1883] = "Fascinating, I was right after all! Those two plants have a common ancestor. Have I told you I\'m a writer?... I\'m currently working on a book about the origin of aggressive plants in Amakna. Reading through old manuscripts, I discovered that before the 150\'s, flowers were friendly, or even obliging! I really wonder what made them become so aggressive!";
D.q[3814] = "A glass of Incarnam Lemonade? It\'s for Brett, isn\'t it? I\'ve seen so many kids like you, I can tell just by looking. More of those experiments? Yeah, well, that old coward won\'t come by and get the lemonade himself... He owes me a few Kamas, he does. But hey, it\'s nothing to do with you, is it? How much do you need, child?";
D.q[1705] = "The Xelor temple is located in the village of Amakna. Talk to Emilie Yuh to begin your training.";
D.q[3539] = "A Feca! Like the rising and falling tide, your wisdom has a gentle but devastating force. I admire your god\'s protecting talents - truly the master of guardians. You, however, have far to go child. I\'ve a task that will help you become stronger...";
D.q[3828] = "I was here before you. If you\'re here, it\'s because you\'re all motivated. But I\'ll only let you through if you have the key to open this door. If you don\'t have it, try to find it on creatures that live in Incarnam.";
D.q[3770] = "You\'re a good kid... a good soldier! Get some rest... and come see me when you feel up to it.";
D.q[3008] = "Go and see Edrige Valling, in the Temple of the goddess Cra, quite a gorgeous chick, believe me!";
D.q[3547] = "May the shadows conceal you, good Sram! That how your kind greet one another, isn\'t it? You prefer to lurk in the shadows... I know the type... like nothing more than slipping a knife firmly into an unsuspecting back ... Just what I\'m looking for!";
D.q[3838] = "So, ready for the adventure of a lifetime?";
D.q[738] = "My friend Rimaraf died in strange circumstances last night, he was poisoned with a Scurvion Rasputin Cake.\nI\'d like you to investigate and find the culprit!";
D.q[7582] = "Would you like to put the rope around your nec...ha ha, sorry, I mean, would you like to put the ring on?";
D.q[1933] = "Hey honey! Am I glad to see your cute little self! Now listen up... My master\'s a little... well... he\'s in bed... no, well he\'s just a little tied up... busy, he\'s busy, okay? So, ehhh, I\'m s\'posed tell you that he\'s got plans for you.  \nAnd take a tip from me... if you\'re in with this guy, you\'re made, honey... Not a thing goes on around here without him knowing...";
D.q[4601] = "My bandana you have found! For ever lost I thought it. From my old friend Sphincter Cell it comes, very dear to me it is. Thank you I should.";
D.q[434] = "My grandfather was living in this village when these creatures invaded. He told me that a Dreggon, if it\'s captured just after its birth, will not be aggressive. But now I\'m getting old, so I can no longer get close enough to Dreggons to steal their eggs.\nI need White Dreggon Eggs, but the only way to get them is to fight them. Do you think you\'re up to the job?";
D.q[4661] = "I can\'t believe it\'s that difficult for you to find the ingredients or get someone to help you. If you don\'t stop fannying around the Bontarians will overtake us.";
D.q[1976] = "I KNEW IT! I was right! Here\'s something in return.";
D.q[1909] = "There you are! My name is Allisteria. Could you give me a hand? I look after this herd of Gobballs, but since all the landslides started happening, it\'s been hard to cope all by myself. ";
D.q[2883] = "First: Get a soul capture spell. This spell can be found in the Akwadala Dungeon.\nSecond: Equip yourself with a Soul Stone.\nThird: Attack the creature you\'re after. Cast your Soul Capture Spell during the fight and win!\nForth: If you kill the creature while your spell is active, then you\'ve got a chance of retrieving the soul of the monster. \n\nObviously, you can\'t recapture the soul of the creature in the arena...";
D.q[414] = "The best way to learn a profession is to find someone who can teach it to you.\nUnfortunately, it\'s difficult to find someone who\'s experienced enough to teach their profession to others.\nThe best idea is to go directly to the Building attached to the Trade Guild you\'re interested in. Then, to become a baker, for instance, all you have to do is go and see Kelog Korflex in the Bakery, or Abely Bobeule in the Carvers Workshop.";
D.q[4674] = "A Brakmarian!! But how did you know the location of the Horn?\nWhatever, I\'ll send you back where you came from! En garde!";
D.q[2658] = "God Xelor gave me the honour of naming me guardian of time. Unless you kill me, there\'s no way you can take my place.";
D.q[1163] = "My job ? Can\'t you see ? I\'m in charge of the larvae. They frighten the poor little rabbits so I\'ve to keep them. Well...between two kips...";
D.q[4573] = "Useless Kamas on this island are. If they were not, even, never enough would you have.";
D.q[3110] = "Thanks for the potatoes. I don\'t like it at all when I run out! I\'d love to have a Twiggy Shovel, then I could grow them myself.";
D.q[3120] = "My mistresses locked the Koolich up in his own cave in order to control Koalak Mountain. To prevent adventurers from setting the Koolich free, we imprisoned the most aggressive and crazy Koalaks too. The Koolich is a quiet creature who\'s said to have become a little mad when the great Skeunk stole his Dofus. A Dofus? You really believe in those things? Anyway, I\'m not here to chat... I must serve my mistresses and guard this entrance!";
D.q[5758] = "My mother\'s birthday is coming up. Have you found a cake she\'d like?";
D.q[5804] = "My name is Hyrkul, I am the terror of Bonta and the immortal champion of the great Djaul. I don\'t like being bothered for nothing. What do you want, pathetic mortal?";
D.q[1324] = "My name is Sbab. I was captured a month ago when your warriors raided Bonta. Once I got there, I had the choice between cooking eternally or dying instantly. You can guess what my answer was.";
D.q[3635] = "You\'re back maggot? The guards are doing their job... that can\'t be right, I know those sons of Bwork too well!";
D.q[6229] = "What? He asked you a favour and then disappeared? It\'s a good thing you found out that the goblins are to blame, or I\'d have had a Gobball lick every orifice in your body.";
D.q[2120] = "Have you seen Jim Fleps by any chance?";
D.q[2132] = "Saketsu will have the results in the wink of an eye.";
D.q[5792] = "My nose is so itchy. You wouldn\'t have a flower on you, would you? It smells of Bloomus!\nOh... that means you\'ve had your time flipped... I\'m very sorry.\n\nWould you like a sweet... some Eniripsa powder, perhaps? For your pets..? Have any of your pets died lately? Well, I can bring them back to life with one simple sneeze! Easy come, easy go.\n\nChoose wisely, though. I can\'t do everything at once!\n";
D.q[2221] = "My poor Tofus! Only an Osamodas could find a remedy to cure them.";
D.q[3718] = "You look pretty strong, could you do me a favour? I need you to bring me some water for my nymphets.";
D.q[6094] = "What? The my cousin\'s descendant is risking life and limb in this cursed Cemetery? My lightning will quickly burst open his doors and grill any creatures who stand in my way.";
D.q[2139] = "Come on, wake up, ya lazy piece of...! Go pass on the message to the other guilds...";
D.q[1925] = "I thank you very much. I\'m sorry about this, but I need something else.";
D.q[4606] = "";
D.q[2165] = "Dates, dates, dates, lallalalalala!";
D.q[4889] = "What? You arrived too late and our soldiers were already defeated? Ugh. We\'re so much weaker than Brakmar... it worries me.";
D.q[2156] = "I\'ve a quest for you.";
D.q[4811] = "My smiths are working on the blade and will soon be finished. But we still need some Golden Scarabugly Leaves. You\'ll find the Golden Scarabugly in the Scaraleaf Dungeon.\nDomen also asked to see you. He\'s really starting to hmmmph me off. But I think we\'ll leave the bickering for another time.";
D.q[3525] = "My son very strong! First goblinmagus.";
D.q[3321] = "Next time I\'ll charge with my Dragoturkeys... I\'ll turn the Bontarian infantry into pulp.";
D.q[2632] = "My son for a meal?... SOLD!\n*He takes the meal and eats it as quick as possible*\nHowever, you\'ll have to go cancel the engagement with the Dento Family Chief.";
D.q[1457] = "Halt! This is the way into the questioning room, nobody can get in without a pass!";
D.q[2311] = "What? You got nothing? No Gobball Legs... No lemons? What are you standing around for? Come on!";
D.q[4154] = "My son, Bugsbo Nee, my sweet beloved wabbit\'s stuck in this abandoned lab and I don\'t know what to do. He won\'t come back and I wouldn\'t dare go and look for him on my own, I\'m too scared of the creatures I might find there.\nCould you go for me?";
D.q[2210] = "I don\'t have time, sonny! Too much wood to sell!";
D.q[3266] = "My son, my little sweetheart disappeared a week ago...\nHe followed some weird old Enutrof on an even weirder island in the North...\nHe brought me this cape from this island, for his mommy he said...\n\n*sniffs*\n\nThen, he left again and followed that Hector Kwismas person and I haven\'t seen him since...\nAnd this senile old man avoids me since that day.\nHe\'s in Madrestam at the moment, if I can find him...\n\n*Shows an old battered shovel*\n\nI\'ll teach him lesson n°2.....";
D.q[4485] = "My spies have just learnt - and not a moment too soon, as usual - that Xephires has been captured. What\'s more, one of our patrols was attacked at the Cemetery of the Tortured. This leads us to believe that they were expecting Xephires and that they were playing with us all along. It\'s a good thing we killed their smith and stole their officers\' weapons. That\'ll even up the odds a bit. We have to gain the upper hand at all costs.";
D.q[4615] = "Bah, you\'re not allowed to answer with another question, that\'s cheating. Are you looking for the Fogornleg Horn too?\nWhat!? You\'re a pathetic Bontarian! Die, scum!";
D.q[6664] = "Be careful, it\'s not a decision to be taken lightly. Do you want to know more before you make your decision?";
D.q[4014] = "Serve a prince, huh? He must be rich if he\'s a prince. How much does he pay?";
D.q[7053] = "Very good, now which gem do you want?";
D.q[4441] = "My spies in Bonta have found someone... to assassinate... The problem is that those airheads didn\'t think they\'d be killing anyone, so they don\'t have any poison on them. You must bring them some, but the only ones who have the poison they need are the Bwork Magi.\nBring this poison to the leader of the spies, he\'s in the South-West of Bonta.";
D.q[7054] = "Very good, now which gem do you want?";
D.q[4572] = "Repeat I will. Insist you must not. Reveal the location never I will.";
D.q[2329] = "My squirrel escaped again! *Boohoo*.\nHe runs away all the time... And I\'m sick of it! I put a \'wanted notice\' on every tree for miles around... Go and read it first. If you see him in Astrub please try to catch him... you can be sure he\'ll fight back, but only cos he\'s frightened...he\'s lovely, really. I don\'t know why the Bow Meows are so scared of him...";
D.q[2309] = "AaaaTTTTttCHOOOOOO! Snirfl! *sniffles loudly*";
D.q[4622] = "Eh, ehhhh! Calm down! I was thinking that one good turn deserves another, but I guess they see things differently over in Brakmar...\nWell, it\'s simple - all I know is that the magic horn is on an island but I don\'t know which one exactly.\nI don\'t know anything else, I\'m not a walking library like Harry Stote.";
D.q[6663] = "There you go, I\'ve drawn it on your map. Just follow your compass and you\'ll be there in no time.";
D.q[437] = "My trainee died in the furnace and I don\' t have anyone else to bring me some wood to heat it up. If you bring me a unit of Ash wood, I\'ll give you some Baker\'s Yeast.\n\nI\'ll also need Sesame Seeds for my next breads. If you bring me five of them, I\'ll give you a Kneader.\nIt\'s an essential tool if you want to become a Baker.";
D.q[2321] = "But you haven\'t done anything? Go and see Dragonsly, he should be able to find something for your bow...";
D.q[4958] = "Very well, but all the material in the world is no good if nobody uses it. I\'m putting you in charge of the workers for the temple. And don\'t just take any old bum off the streets of Brakmar either. Oh, by the way - I need a lot of hands!";
D.q[2330] = "Hello! Welcome to my market! I hope you\'ll find everything you need. How can I help you?";
D.q[2343] = "Such bad luck! There\'s no way we can get any closer, see?";
D.q[1503] = "We\'re keeping an eye on this side. Earth is within rope range or accessible with a good teleport. So be careful!";
D.q[4678] = "Ahh, my equipment has arrived. Thank Oto for me, please. Er, actually, maybe don\'t thank him... he might not like that.";
D.q[1676] = "Very well, now turn the Gobball Wheel!";
D.q[2376] = "I can only teach you one specialty - either wand, staff or bow sculpting. But if you\'re very dedicated and have a lot of time, you might manage to do two of them.";
D.q[4188] = "Did you confront the Black and Pink Knight for me?";
D.q[2377] = "Are you sure you want to start a career as a Bow Carver?";
D.q[263] = "Bernardo Pull rents a room up there for himself and his Dopples. He\'s often looking for someone to fight with them, go up and ask him about it if you\'re feeling brave.";
D.q[4630] = "Do what you must to get the turtle talking. Get to it!";
D.q[2382] = "Are you sure you want to start a career as a Sword smith?";
D.q[4682] = "My spies have confirmed that the Bontarians have the Fogornleg Horn. They won\'t wait long before using it against us so hurry up and equip the militia.";
D.q[6448] = "My uncle Starky is gonna come save me, and he\'ll give you a kicking too, believe me. I\'m not surprised that the Brakmarians are all so aggressive now that I\'ve seen the pits they live in. It\'s no wonder they\'re jealous of Bonta\'s magnificence.";
D.q[3484] = "What are you doing in my hole? Is your mother off her head too? Bworkcelhain threw me here... my own mother!";
D.q[6705] = "My uncle had to escape without me but he\'ll live to fight another day, and that day, he\'ll come with his cavalry and raze this building and this whole stinking city to thhe ground. You\'ll see.";
D.q[4160] = "My wife... She left, god knows where. What am I going to do now? What\'s time without her? What\'s all those people I don\'t care about now that she\'s gone? \nEven though I\'m one of the most distinguished scientists and one of the most respected of Otomai\'s disciples, I can\'t do anything without my wife! I could take you where I last saw her and maybe you could look for her... And if you find her, you could try and convince her to come back.";
D.q[5111] = "Things are coming along nicely, all except for these CURSED chains. I just need to find a few disciples, then I can finally set up my order and stand shoulder to shoulder with Djaul. The last task I have for you is this. Go and find at least three disciples for me. Look in all the important places in Brakmar for a start.";
D.q[2396] = "Are you sure you want to become a lumberjack? You can be my apprentice but you need to be motivated!";
D.q[6396] = "And here\'s the result! Without me you would never have completed the back-scratcher, admit that I\'m the greatest blacksmith in Brakmar.\nYou got what you wanted? Then get out!";
D.q[3378] = "My, my, you\'re a brave one... you have done it. Your courage shines upon you like the burning summer sun. Walk towards your destiny and may your soul be strong and unmoveable. Leave me alone now, My turnip soup is boiling over.";
D.q[2406] = "Ahah! Here comes another apprentice! To start with, you\'ll need a leather cutter. I can sell you one, one of these days. Once you have it, use our comfortable workbenches which are especially designed for the cutting of leather. Start with easy designs, here, I\'ll draw them in your shoemaker\'s notebook.";
D.q[4627] = "I can\'t wait to have that horn... finally I\'ll be able to raze Bonta to the ground and rebuild the world our way!";
D.q[2410] = "Hi, I\'m just a young apprentice... If you want to know more about our art, go and see Dragonsly. He spends all his time in the marketplace since it opened not so long ago.";
D.q[6543] = "If you want an answer to your question you must first place a bet.\nHow much do you want to bet?";
D.q[3340] = "My, my, you\'re a great little adventurer... I just... we are more than associates aren\'t we... I just wanted to know if... oh blast! Blast it all. Here! Take this as some repayment for all we\'ve been through. I knew you did not... just leave, please.";
D.q[3671] = "My, my... you\'re far too strong to stay in this part of the World of Twelve. I don\'t have any more missions for you. Off you go and look for the Dofus.";
D.q[6521] = "You haven\'t bet very much, are you scared of losing or something?";
D.q[2431] = "Thankyousomuch!!! You saved my life!";
D.q[1126] = "I\'m the greatest, the most magical and gifted of all smithmagi in the world. My weapons are ultra powerful and each of them is totally unique. And you, what do you want?";
D.q[4593] = "... leave me here!? But in my state I\'ll...\nAh! A Bontarian has already caught up with me!";
D.q[7581] = "";
D.q[4883] = "You can tell Amayiro he can count on me and my men to help.";
D.q[244] = "Let me warn you. That labyrinth is stuffed with monsters, and stuffed with the spirits of all the dumb adventurers who died there, too. They now haunt that dark and hostile place. You\'d best have a neck like a Bwork\'s crotch if you plan on going in there.";
D.q[1952] = "That\'s kind.";
D.q[1910] = "Myyyyyy soft tooooy, boohoooh, someone stole my soft toy! I had so much trouble winning it at the Trool Fair...Can you help me get it back? Those thieves...in the forest North of the village, they\'ve...they\'ve assaulted me, and they stole myyy soft tooooy...";
D.q[6399] = "Yuck. Just hearing its name makes me feel sick. Have you got any more?";
D.q[725] = "Negotiate for some powder with Moob Tsinhcetoryp. Our new cannons have left our warehouse and we will test them during our next assault on Brakmar.\nYou\'ll pay for it this time. So be tactful when negotiating the price. I need about 10 pods of it.";
D.q[2451] = "Nice one, mercenary.";
D.q[2452] = "Ah big shrew! Well done!";
D.q[7069] = "Nah sir, there\'s nuthin\' behind me. It\'s just a empty cave. And why do I stay here in front of an empty cave? Good question. A Iop will answer that better than me, cos\' his head\'ll be empty. Well, let me tell you... I\'m a kindly Sram, and that\'s somethin\' you don\'t see every day. I just don\'t want people comin\' into this cave an\' wastin\' their time, that\'s all. There\'s nuthin\' here. Don\'t believe all this nonsense about it bein\' a hideout or nuthin... it\'s all lies, lies I tell ya!";
D.q[3302] = "The Demon Lord erected a new building - in one night! An edifice dedicated to knowledge, war, power, supremacy and strategy.";
D.q[1532] = "It\'s a private house, only those who know their way around know the code number to get in.";
D.q[2084] = "Nepra\'s not here...You\'re looking for Subosycold? Sure! He would still be more courteous from the Enutrofs to come and ask it for themselves. Oh, well, I haven\'t found the remedy against this obsessive scourge that makes them dig in places they shouldn\'t.";
D.q[2476] = "Well, we just have to fill all that in now! Thanks a lot!";
D.q[2475] = "Amber? You don\'t find this on any old tree, do you? You should ask a Treechnid, I\'m pretty sure it\'ll be happy to give you some... (grins).";
D.q[2488] = "It\'s you again!? Remember, I need five bits of amber!";
D.q[2489] = "Ello, ello! \'Ave you seen Toyo Dzink by any chance? He\'s a mate of mine... looking for Amber, he was, now I\'m lookin\' for him... I\'ve heard he might be on the road between Astrub and Amakna. But there\'s no amber there, he shoulda gone South! He\'d be very grateful if you gave him some. ";
D.q[2487] = "Heeeyyy Amber! Thank you! Here is your reward!";
D.q[25] = "Hi, I\'m Kelog Hornflex, renowned Baker of Amakna.\nI\'ve some little tasks for you to do if you\'re interested.";
D.q[2492] = "Hey ho! It\'s off to work we go.";
D.q[2516] = "... everyone can now get to the Dofus Receptacle! A lot of people want to see it and buy souvenirs of our island! *Rubs his hands.* Thank god for the Grandapan! Mmh.... Can I help you?";
D.q[2520] = "Mumble... Dofus... mumble... Grandapan... mumble... World conquest... mumblemumble.... gwahahaha!";
D.q[5910] = "Never leave me again. Let me guess... Divad needs me again and it\'s you he\'s sending with the news?";
D.q[2207] = "Never mind, but you don\'t know what you\'re missing. Go and see Clint Pot, will you? He should be able to help you...\nI\'ve shown you the way. Just keep an eye on your compass.";
D.q[3317] = "Next time I charge with my Dragoturkeys, I\'ll break through the very walls of Brakmar.";
D.q[2562] = "Among the Dofus awe fake ones... Genuine Dofus awe laid by dwagons. Only dummies can think Cawwots lay eggs! The Cawwot Dofus is an enchanted Cawwot by Wa Wabbit which gives it enormous powers...";
D.q[2695] = "Nice to meet you! I don\'t want to boast but I courageously protected my town, the beautiful city of Astrub, against an invasion of gross little creatures! Anyway. I\'ve heard your conversation with the Shaman - a nice Pandawa fellow. You should go see Grandapan. He\'s the one calling the shots around here.";
D.q[2583] = "Halt! You can\'t go through!";
D.q[3388] = "Nice weather, huh! I feel like cuttin\' down a tree or two. If I\'m really lucky, I migh\' even come across a Treechnid!";
D.q[2073] = "No ? Really ? Too bad, you don\'t know what you\'re missing!";
D.q[2497] = "No Pandarista tax, no Pandala! As simple as that!";
D.q[262] = "As a Cra, you can go up to the second floor, but my Dopple trainer is staying there at the moment.";
D.q[2610] = "Finally, we\'re at the end of the first chapter of this bloody scroll!  \nThe next tunnel looks particularly complicated! \nWhat\'s this... ridiculous, there\'s a warning saying: It\'s best to wear a Sue-Dough-Ku necklace!";
D.q[2618] = "You find father Metoassa and convince him?";
D.q[2619] = "Grmph...";
D.q[2557] = "No need to lie, impudent vermin! Those evil eggs spread violence and devastation wherever they go! Don\'t get me wrong: a dragon egg woudn\'t hurt a Moskito: it\'s the whole group of greedy adventurers - to which you belong - who need to be exterminated... don\'t you think?";
D.q[2131] = "No news from Dragonsly. Are you sure you gave him the blood of that... bloody dark miner?";
D.q[2667] = "If you wanna trade items with me, move five steps back, and put them on the ground. I\'ll do the same.... Hihihi!";
D.q[6277] = "No problem! You see guys, I know how to handle the women. And that\'s exactly why I\'m the boss. \nRight, let\'s get down to business. You come back and see me tomorrow night, I\'ll make sure that the guys are at the inn and that they leave us alone. You\'ll see, cutie, the nimbleness of the Srams is no exaggeration.";
D.q[1069] = "No problaim, me fiend. Com bak enytaime.";
D.q[2006] = "Have you lost your Dizbi Flower? That\'s such a waste! Well, I give you another one, take care of it, it sure is a precious thing!";
D.q[712] = "The drudges I currently coach aren\'t exactly brilliant... would you mind showing me what you can do in fight?";
D.q[3217] = "I doubt you know the Labyrinth of the Minotoror - you don\'t look like you\'ve been out of your own backyard much!\nWell, it\'s true that I\'ve never been out of this cave, but that\'s different.\nThis maze is similar to the Minotoror... it\'s cursed and adventurers who head inside usually suffer from memory loss and forget where they last saved their position. Recall potions are useless if you want to get out of this maze. Luckily for you I\'ll stay by your side to guide you through this mess! I\'ve been trained by the best guide and archaeologist in the whole continent: the famous, the outstanding, the potbellied Lorkos! All he ever said to tourists he took in the maze was \"Don\'t worry! I know the way!\" Hehehe, the silly old fool! He got lost in his own museum! Anyway... I feel like I\'m wasting my breath.";
D.q[3397] = "No time! Niiiiihhhhh! Leave me alone!";
D.q[2744] = "I can see by youw feet that you walked a long way to come visit me. How can I help you?";
D.q[2747] = "Do you realise what\'s going on? To keep them fresh, you have to gather Bamboo with your tail. It\'s hard enough with your hands! Anyway! I\'d rather pick up some Bamboo than swindle adventurers. Some of the merchants are downright liars. I wouldn\'t be surprised if they tried to sell you a Dofus laid by a Dragoturkey. Know what I mean...";
D.q[5703] = "No! Wait. There\'s a statuette hidden in Amakna Mine. You\'ll need to use powerful magic to reveal it.";
D.q[2755] = "If you can answer some questions about the Art of Pandawushu, and if you\'re skilled enough, you\'ll obtain the grade.";
D.q[2784] = "Kweeeeh *kof kof*";
D.q[2798] = "The call of the wild, the cursed wild, is calling you, isn\'t it?";
D.q[5681] = "No, no and no again! I can\'t work in these conditions. Merlinmagus do this, Merlinmagus do that. Merlinmagus I have a sore tooth!!! I\'ve had ENOUGH!";
D.q[1158] = "No, eagles of Tainela don\'t need the code to enter your house. Don\'t forget they have wings! Never give your code to anyone!";
D.q[1536] = "Here are 2,000 Kamas to show our appreciation. The workers will be pleased to know they can continue working.";
D.q[2801] = "... \nEmerald is the colour...\nRazeriane gazes at her beauty in the smooth shell of the Dofus...\n...Go away now...";
D.q[2814] = "Mmh, You\'ve got a LONG way to go... A Kwan is a short question that the Master asks his Disciple.";
D.q[282] = "Hee Hee! You\'re impressed by my evil intelligence, aren\'t you? You want to join my group? Very well... but you\'ll have to bring me 80 evil dandelion flowers. I\'ll make you one of us and I\'ll reward you well. These dandelions are the only flowers that are in harmony with my prodigious intelligence.";
D.q[6499] = "No, please... you wouldn\'t hurt a crazy old man, would you? I\'ll tell you everything I know and... yes, take anything you want from my jewellers shop.";
D.q[4237] = "No, no, you\'re mistaken. I don\'t speak of the monster of the peat bog. It has been there time out of mind. It too may be linked to the Plasmogrine, a parallel evolution perhaps. Anything is possible on this island! The monster of the peat bog is the least of our worries...";
D.q[6405] = "No, why\'d do you ask me that?";
